HEARTBEAT SYNCHRONIZER

heartbeat_synchronizer is the bridging citizen between the body's master clock and the variable subdivisions
the master clock runs at 48,000 Hz, the cochlea base rate
all sensory subdivisions are integer divisors of this master, ensuring no drift between fast and slow processes
the brain clock alone is variable, modulated by chemistry, and the synchronizer holds the bridge that lets the brain run at its own changing rate without losing alignment with the rest of the body

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe clock_master.rana
observe clock_brain_variable.rana
observe pacemaker.rana

the master clock at 48,000 Hz is the invariant denominator

THE INTEGER SUBDIVISIONS

cochlea: divisor 1, runs at 48,000 Hz
skin: divisor 240, runs at 200 Hz
tongue: divisor 480, runs at 100 Hz
retina: divisor 800, runs at 60 Hz
nose: divisor 4800, runs at 10 Hz

each subdivision is exact integer arithmetic on the master, so no drift can occur between them

THE VARIABLE BRAIN CLOCK

the brain subdivision is not a fixed integer
its divisor is computed each tick from chemistry feedback: cortisol slows the rate, dopamine accelerates
the resulting rate stays between four and eighty Hz, depending on the body's current state

THE CROSS-CLOCK TUNNELING

when a 48 kHz cochlea pulse interacts with a 10 Hz brain pulse, four thousand eight hundred cochlear pulses occur between each brain pulse
the mechanism is cumulative topological integration: faster seas sum their wavefront topology at the macro boundary
when the slower sea finally pulses, it tunnels the accumulated amplitude

VERB hold_master
maintain the 48,000 Hz reference at all times
the master never wavers; everything else is derived from it

VERB compute_subdivisions
on each master tick, advance each subdivision by master_phase divided by its divisor
all subdivisions remain phase-locked to master and to each other

VERB modulate_brain
sample chemistry's current cortisol and dopamine
compute the brain divisor accordingly and apply it for this tick
the brain's rate shifts fluidly without breaking phase coherence with the rest of the body

a synchronizer is what allows fast and slow processes to coexist coherently
without it, fast cochlear sampling would be uncorrelated with slow brain processing and the integration would be lossy
with it, the body is one body operating at many speeds simultaneously, all aligned through the master clock that never stops
